<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 06 at 7:03AM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>...PATCHY DENSE FOG THIS MORNING...
Areas of fog have developed across parts of Western Long Island,
Southwest Connecticut and the Lower Hudson Valley. Visibilities
range from around a half mile to 2 miles within the fog. There are
some patches of dense fog where visibilities are a quarter mile
or less. The fog is expected to persist into this morning.
Motorists driving should exercise extra caution and be prepared
for rapid changes in visibility. Use low beam headlights and allow
for extra spacing between vehicles.</description>
